snippet.textDisplay: Middle School was actually the best time of my life. I had finally gotten over my parents divorce when I was in Grade 4. When I went to middle school, I had been diagnosed with depression and was on medications that actually worked, I am a high functioning autistic and until Grade 7 I had no friends because I just didn't know how to communicate with kids my own age till then. From Grade 7-9 I had an incredibly supportive and close knit group of friends that were all Gothic like myself. I was still riding horses competitively on my own horse, Bueno who was my best friend. I even went to my Aunties house every weekend and was uber health conscious and worked out all the time. But then high school happened and my life was destroyed. At age 14 I was kicked out of my house by my step father and my mom and was put in group homes. My life's been a wreck ever since then. I've been hospitalized 27 times since Grade 10 in Psychiatric units in various hospitals. Got re diagnosed as Having scitzo-affective disorder with PTSD, Severe Anxiety, and OCD tendancies as well as full blown psychosis. I had two kids that were taken away because of the Fucked up child protection here where I live because of my mental illness diagnosis they thought I wouldn't be able to take care of my own children and took them both at birth. And now I have full blown agoraphobia. I barely leave my house. I wish I could go back to middle school, when my life was happier and I had real friends and real family relationships...

snippet.textDisplay:
Great video as always. I have been looking around for a way to contact your team privately as I have some feedback that I would rather not be public, but I was unsuccessful. So I will post my story here and hope the internet doesn't eviscerate me.




I have experienced a lot of trauma related to pornography. In this day and age references to, and discussions of, pornography are common in all forms of media. In regards to most television shows, there is no real way to let the producers know that there are people out there with this kind of experience, and so I've resigned myself to living with near daily triggers of my traumatic experience. However, the main thing youtube brings to its creators and audience is an interactive platform, so I thought I might as well take the chance and let the team know that this affects my ability to enjoy the channel as a whole.


I hope it doesn't come across as a morality judgement in any way. That is not my intention. I just have a particular experience, and I know I'm not the only one.


Thanks for your time.


Also a general email address might benefit audience members.
